(15338, 3056, 'movie_plot', 'Directed by renowned director Ann Hui, A Simple Life is the restrained yet powerful human drama about an elderly maid, Sister Tao, and Roger, the young master of the family she devoted her life to. After suffering a stroke, Sister Tao realizes that it is time for her to retire. As she struggles to adjust to her new life at the nursing home, Roger decides to be there to take care of the woman who has devoted her life to raising him.\r\nFor her inspirational performance as Sister Tao, veteran actress Deanie Ip was awarded the honors of Best Actress at the Venice Film Festival.'),
